article.headline: CS Bakersfield 70, Cal Poly-SLO 63
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Stephon Carter scored 22 points, including making 14 tries from the line, to lead Cal State Bakersfield over Cal Poly 70-63 on Thursday night. Santwon Latunde added 13 points for the Roadrunners (2-10), while Trent Blakley scored 12 points and Donald Johnson pulled down 11 rebounds. The Roadrunners went into halftime up 29-22, a lead the Mustangs (3-8) were not able to overcome despite scoring 41 points in the second period. Will Taylor picked up a double-double, scoring 10 points and pulling down 12 rebounds for the Mustangs. Starters Lorenzo Keeler and Jordan Lewis also finished with double-digit days, scoring 17 and 10 points respectively.
